717360f-b.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 26th Street
717360f-b.text:
Broadway, south from 26th Street. Fifth Avenue is to the
left and intersects this thoroughfare at 23rd Street. The apex
formed at that point is occupied by the triangular Fuller (Flat-
iron) Building. To the left appears the low white structure
that was the former Hotel Bartholdi: View 2 is photographed
from 25th Street, being closer to the aforementioned features.
The street clock is in front of the 5th Avenue Building.
June 15, 1937
Views 1,2
Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project
Same view farther south.

731181f-a.title: Celebrations - Parades - Municipal events - Decoration Day Parade.
731181f-a.text:
Celebrations, Parades and Municipal Events: A contingent of
girls in the 1894 Decoration Day Parade. Buildings in the back-
ground are on the west side of Broadway, at 26th Street.
May 30, 1894.
The Illustrated American
